text:
*Hi everyone,* 
I am Maria, writing to you if you have any knowledge on HS cookies triggers
We’re managing cookies using 3rd party platform and want to prevent non-essential cookies from firing before user consent. A few questions:
• To manage non-essential cookies via our 3rd-party tool, we need to enable HubSpot cookie tracking. Does this activate the HubSpot cookie banner? (We’d like to avoid this since a CMP is already implemented.)
• How can we stop non-essential cookies (analytics, performance, functional, advertising) from triggering pre-consent?
    ◦ These cookies can not be edited through the CMP 
Thanks in advance for your guidance! :star:
